comments.body:
@rhatdan @mheon @baude adding collection of logs is pretty easy: just [cat the file in it's own `script` section](https://console.cloud.google.com/compute/instancesDetail/zones/us-central1-a/instances/cirrus-task-5764209857003520?project=libpod-218412&folder&organizationId) (so it's separated in the WebUI).  Note: It needs to be added in two places, once for success and the other in case of failure.

Question:  For rootless testing and podman-in-podman, also grab ``audit.log`` from the host?

'nother Question:  Assuming I can get `audit.log` working, what else shall I grab while I'm at it?
